## Completed Work This Session

### Project: blanch — All 5 phases (Tasks #804-808)
Python drop-in replacement for bleach HTML sanitization library (52.4M downloads/month, deprecated Jan 2023). Zero dependencies, Python 3.10+, uses stdlib html.parser.

Core: HTML parser/tokenizer with security hardening (null byte stripping, nesting depth limits, malformed HTML handling). Cleaner class + clean() function matching bleach.clean() signature exactly (tags, attributes, protocols, strip, strip_comments, css_sanitizer). Linker class + linkify() function matching bleach.linkify() (callbacks, skip_tags, parse_email, build_url_re, build_email_re, DEFAULT_CALLBACKS with nofollow). CSSSanitizer class for style attribute sanitization.

Compat layer: blanch.compat.bleach module re-exports all public APIs for `import blanch.compat.bleach as bleach`.

168 tests across 7 test files including OWASP XSS vector tests. mypy strict + ruff clean. CI green on Python 3.10-3.13 (ubuntu + macos). MIT license.

